1
00:00:37,433 --> 00:00:38,700
<i> I admit.</i>

2
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:44,367
<i>This is the only thing missing
for me to love you again.</i>

3
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:48,200
<i> And this time,</i>

4
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:51,867
<i>I will fight
for my love for you.</i>

5
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:55,933
<i> I will take you back...</i>

6
00:00:56,067 --> 00:00:58,233
<i>from the woman
who stole you from me.</i>

7
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:02,033
<i>I thought you
would only take Dad's papers.</i>

8
00:01:02,167 --> 00:01:03,933
<i>Why are you packing his stuff,
too?</i>

9
00:01:04,067 --> 00:01:05,667
<i>Because once
Dad's out of the hospital,</i>

10
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:07,133
<i>we will move into the apartment.</i>

11
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,767
<i>You will take him away from us?</i>

12
00:01:08,900 --> 00:01:10,200
<i> You take after your mom.</i>

13
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:12,067
<i> You're just as mean as she is.</i>

14
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,767
<i> You're worse than me, Coleen!</i>

15
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:16,600
<i>You always hurt me!
You always pick a fight with me!</i>

16
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:17,400
<i> Go ahead!</i>

17
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:19,867
<i>Hurt me! Do your worst, Coleen!</i>

18
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:21,700
<i> Because it will be your last.</i>

19
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:23,167
<i> I will fight for my rights</i>

20
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:25,900
<i>as Dad's legal daughter
from now on, Coleen.</i>

21
00:01:26,033 --> 00:01:32,033
<i>You can never get near him.
You can't visit him anymore.</i>

22
00:01:33,367 --> 00:01:34,100
<i> Coleen!</i>

23
00:01:34,233 --> 00:01:36,200
<i> Jessica!</i>

24
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:38,133
<i>- Wait!
- Stop it!</i>

25
00:01:38,267 --> 00:01:40,033
<i> I hope you can forgive me</i>

26
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,867
<i>for all the times
I disrespected you.</i>

27
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,333
<i> Dad, I'm sorry.</i>

28
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:47,000
<i> Please wake up.</i>

29
00:01:47,133 --> 00:01:48,467
<i> Mom, food trip.</i>

30
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:50,600
<i>You're delaying my return
to the ICU.</i>

31
00:01:50,733 --> 00:01:53,133
<i>To keep me
from catching those traitors.</i>

32
00:01:53,267 --> 00:01:55,033
<i> You're being paranoid, Mom.</i>

33
00:01:55,167 --> 00:01:56,400
<i> We'll see about that.</i>

34
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:58,000
<i> Wait! Wait!</i>

35
00:01:58,133 --> 00:02:01,500
<i>Get out of my way if you
don't want to get hurt.</i>

36
00:02:01,633 --> 00:02:02,867
<i> Mom!</i>

37
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:08,333
Mom! Mom, please!
Let's eat first.

38
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:10,000
I don't want to waste
the food I ordered.

39
00:02:10,133 --> 00:02:10,733
- Please!
- Stop!

40
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:12,333
We'll eat after I make sure

41
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:14,867
you didn't let the illegitimate
family go into the ICU.

42
00:02:15,033 --> 00:02:16,067
Mom! Mom, wait!

43
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:16,967
Mom, please.

44
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,467
- Mom.
- Don't block my way.

45
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:20,033
- Move!
- Mom!

46
00:02:20,167 --> 00:02:22,000
I said, out of my way!

47
00:02:43,167 --> 00:02:44,600
Okay.

48
00:02:44,733 --> 00:02:46,600
Let's go back to the cafeteria.

49
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:54,067
Jessica, let's go.

50
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,600
I thought you were hungry.

51
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:04,100
So, you were able to visit
your dad.

52
00:03:05,933 --> 00:03:08,033
Your half-sister
is a good person after all.

53
00:03:08,167 --> 00:03:09,567
She helped you.

54
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:13,667
But why...

55
00:03:15,033 --> 00:03:16,400
don't you look happy?

56
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,867
It's as if
no one's really listening to me.

57
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,700
Dad is still unconscious.

58
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:29,967
I want to hear his voice again.

59
00:03:34,233 --> 00:03:35,533
I want...

60
00:03:37,633 --> 00:03:39,400
to hear him calling me Andeng.

61
00:03:40,533 --> 00:03:41,500
At least,

62
00:03:42,567 --> 00:03:43,933
you were able to hold him.

63
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:47,367
I want to feel
Dad's embrace again.

64
00:03:52,433 --> 00:03:54,733
I want to feel
his presence again.

65
00:03:56,933 --> 00:03:58,667
<i>I only have a two-year contract.
It'll pass by quickly.</i>

66
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:02,200
<i>I'll go home once I've saved up
enough money. Okay?</i>

67
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:11,633
Come here.

68
00:04:13,467 --> 00:04:14,967
For now,

69
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:16,900
let me be the one to hold you...

70
00:04:18,733 --> 00:04:20,033
until he can.

71
00:04:32,733 --> 00:04:35,100
Be patient. You'll get there.

72
00:05:03,267 --> 00:05:04,867
What are you doing?

73
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,267
Isn't it obvious?

74
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:09,933
I'm trying to stop you
from getting near Manuel.

75
00:05:11,367 --> 00:05:12,633
What?

76
00:05:12,767 --> 00:05:14,033
Are you deaf

77
00:05:14,167 --> 00:05:15,500
or pretending to be one?

78
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:19,300
You can never get
near my husband again.

79
00:05:25,433 --> 00:05:27,433
Jessica,

80
00:05:27,567 --> 00:05:31,100
did you tell your mom
to stop us from seeing Dad?

81
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:35,600
- Let us in, if not...
- If not, what?

82
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:38,233
Are you going to hurt me?

83
00:05:39,167 --> 00:05:40,433
Go ahead.

84
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:42,500
I won't fight,

85
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:43,933
but...

86
00:05:44,067 --> 00:05:46,633
don't blame me
if I send you to jail.

87
00:05:46,767 --> 00:05:48,067
You're so evil.

88
00:05:49,467 --> 00:05:50,667
Wow.

89
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,700
Coming from you?

90
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:55,900
Aren't you oppressing
and hurting my daughter?

91
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:57,833
You should do
some self-reflection.

92
00:05:59,467 --> 00:06:00,833
Stop it, Hazel.

93
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:04,367
We have an agreement.

94
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:05,800
Oh, yes.

95
00:06:05,933 --> 00:06:08,433
It was just a one-time deal.

96
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,967
One-time deal?

97
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:15,067
Fine.

98
00:06:16,067 --> 00:06:20,600
Then I'll file the lawsuit
against you and this hospital.

99
00:06:21,867 --> 00:06:23,500
Sure.

100
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:25,400
You might just get embarrassed.

101
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:27,400
Why?

102
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:39,467
Nurse Miles,

103
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:46,400
I accept that Hazel just
accidentally pushed my daughter.

104
00:06:46,533 --> 00:06:48,333
I won't file a lawsuit anymore.

105
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,467
You accept that what happened
was an accident.

106
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,967
And now you're filing a case?

107
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:56,767
One more thing.

108
00:06:56,900 --> 00:07:01,000
Who will prove
that I pushed your daughter?

109
00:07:06,167 --> 00:07:07,867
What now?

110
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,767
Bet that shut you up, huh?

111
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:12,500
You won't outsmart me, Felma.

112
00:07:12,633 --> 00:07:14,167
Not me.

113
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:16,867
Now, enjoy being this close
while you can.

114
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:18,900
Because my lawyer
is already filing

115
00:07:19,033 --> 00:07:21,700
a restraining order against you.

116
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:36,433
Jessica...

117
00:07:36,567 --> 00:07:38,167
let's go.

118
00:07:55,567 --> 00:07:57,333
They thought they could
still get near Manuel.

119
00:07:57,467 --> 00:07:59,100
Never.

120
00:07:59,233 --> 00:08:00,033
You know me.

121
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:01,600
I planned all of this.

122
00:08:01,733 --> 00:08:04,900
I'm not just one,
but two steps ahead.

123
00:08:05,033 --> 00:08:07,700
What do you mean
by two steps?

124
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:10,567
Remember my call
with Mr. Wilson?

125
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:12,033
Yes. What about it?

126
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:15,267
Nurse Hazel! There you are!
I've been looking for you.

127
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,100
Hold on.

128
00:08:17,233 --> 00:08:19,133
- Why? What happened?
- It's about your husband.

129
00:08:19,267 --> 00:08:21,133
- What?
- He's already awake.

130
00:08:22,167 --> 00:08:23,700
Really?

131
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,200
- Jessica.
- Mom.

132
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:36,867
- Dad's awake, Mom.
- Dear.

133
00:08:38,133 --> 00:08:39,567
My dear.

134
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:41,800
Mom. Mom, he's awake.

135
00:08:41,933 --> 00:08:43,400
Dad is awake.

136
00:08:43,533 --> 00:08:45,233
Thank you, God. Thank you.

137
00:08:45,367 --> 00:08:46,533
Thank you.

138
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,367
Come on.

139
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:52,333
Let's get changed.

140
00:08:52,467 --> 00:08:53,667
Yes, Mom.

141
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:07,367
Doc! Doc, I heard
my husband is awake.

142
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,200
Hazel.

143
00:09:09,333 --> 00:09:10,933
Manuel is improving.

144
00:09:11,067 --> 00:09:11,967
Manuel is improving.

145
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:13,600
Thank you so much.

146
00:09:13,733 --> 00:09:15,433
- Manuel.
- Doc.

147
00:09:15,567 --> 00:09:16,833
Doc...

148
00:09:16,967 --> 00:09:18,333
where is my wife?

149
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:20,800
I want to see her.

150
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:26,100
Doc, where's Felma?

151
00:09:57,867 --> 00:09:59,133
Yes, Jeff.

152
00:09:59,267 --> 00:10:01,100
Please take care
of Mom and Coleen.

153
00:10:03,133 --> 00:10:04,500
What happened?

154
00:10:05,633 --> 00:10:08,000
That Hazel...

155
00:10:08,133 --> 00:10:10,867
is prohibiting us
from seeing Dad again!

156
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,433
- I don't understand why.
- Andrea, breathe.

157
00:10:16,567 --> 00:10:19,167
Calm down. Calm down.

158
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:20,600
Now I get it...

159
00:10:20,733 --> 00:10:23,600
why Jessica was in such a hurry
to get me in the ICU.

160
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:26,400
Because Hazel
was about to shut me out again.

161
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:28,333
Would you like me...

162
00:10:28,467 --> 00:10:30,167
to talk to Hazel?

163
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:31,500
Who knows?

164
00:10:31,633 --> 00:10:33,167
She might fall for my charm.

165
00:10:36,933 --> 00:10:38,000
Sorry.

166
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:42,033
It was a really bad joke.
I only want...

167
00:10:42,167 --> 00:10:43,533
to make you feel better.

168
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:46,567
That's not it.

169
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:48,067
I just realized

170
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:51,333
I'm dragging you into my problem
again. I don't want that.

171
00:10:53,167 --> 00:10:56,633
I know
you genuinely want to help.

172
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:00,367
And...

173
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:02,300
you're not going to face
a human being.

174
00:11:03,567 --> 00:11:04,833
A demon.

175
00:11:04,967 --> 00:11:06,900
I can handle that.

176
00:11:07,033 --> 00:11:09,600
Angels always defeat
demons, right?

177
00:11:10,633 --> 00:11:11,900
Another bad joke?

178
00:11:12,033 --> 00:11:13,333
Hey.

179
00:11:13,467 --> 00:11:14,967
Don't I look like an angel?

180
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,033
Don't I?

181
00:11:19,167 --> 00:11:20,133
There.

182
00:11:20,267 --> 00:11:22,100
That's what I like.

183
00:11:22,233 --> 00:11:25,000
I can still make you smile
even though you're worried.

184
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:28,100
You really are heaven-sent,
Joel.

185
00:11:28,233 --> 00:11:31,400
See? You admitted
that I'm an angel.

186
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:42,533
Jessica, dear.

187
00:11:44,567 --> 00:11:46,400
Where's your Aunt Felma?

188
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:50,300
Don't worry.

189
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:52,600
I'll call her later.

190
00:11:52,733 --> 00:11:55,500
I'll let her know you're awake.

191
00:11:57,833 --> 00:11:59,633
Why isn't she here?

192
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,967
Felma's busy.

193
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:09,067
She's taking care of the...

194
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:11,000
people that Andrea has scammed.

195
00:12:12,567 --> 00:12:16,567
And also the person
who ran you over.

196
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:25,033
She gave me the responsibility.

197
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,700
She said...

198
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:31,100
I'm the one who should
take care of you now.

199
00:12:37,433 --> 00:12:38,633
Manuel.

200
00:12:42,133 --> 00:12:43,533
Manuel, I hope...

201
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:47,367
you can see my efforts.

202
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:52,967
When I prayed,

203
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:56,533
I said...

204
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:59,867
I'd do everything
so you could recover.

205
00:13:01,567 --> 00:13:04,200
So we can start all over again.

206
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,667
Even though it hurts,

207
00:13:10,733 --> 00:13:12,100
I'll do everything...

208
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:16,033
to make you happy.

209
00:13:16,167 --> 00:13:22,333
Don't worry, once you're okay
and no longer in the ICU,

210
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:24,967
I will ask Felma to come over.
Okay?

211
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,533
So she can visit you...

212
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:30,533
once you're in a regular room.

213
00:13:30,667 --> 00:13:32,567
So, Manuel,

214
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:34,100
please...

215
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:36,200
get better.

216
00:14:07,867 --> 00:14:10,500
Ma'am, what is it?

217
00:14:10,633 --> 00:14:12,433
Temporary Restraining Order.

218
00:14:13,633 --> 00:14:15,400
That evil woman is so cunning.

219
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:18,667
How did she file
it so quickly?

220
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:21,467
Her accomplice is
a police officer.

221
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:24,600
She said it the last time
she stormed in here.

222
00:14:24,733 --> 00:14:26,533
For sure, they
pulled some strings.

223
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,400
And Hazel's working
at the hospital, remember?

224
00:14:30,567 --> 00:14:33,233
They probably
supported her.

225
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:38,733
It's Jessica.

226
00:14:40,067 --> 00:14:41,400
I told you.

227
00:14:42,467 --> 00:14:45,067
For sure, she's now working
with her Mom.

228
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:48,167
I hope you believe me now.

229
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,167
She wants to ruin us.

230
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:54,533
Sweetie, don't accuse
your sister.

231
00:14:54,667 --> 00:14:56,500
She can't do anything
about that.

232
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:00,467
Yes. And she let Andrea
in the ICU.

233
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:03,667
Mom, we're going to fight.

234
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:06,033
I won't let Hazel win.

235
00:15:08,667 --> 00:15:10,433
Why don't you eat first?

236
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,533
Go on.

237
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:25,633
Doc, when can I bring
my husband home?

238
00:15:25,767 --> 00:15:27,533
Are you serious, Hazel?

239
00:15:28,633 --> 00:15:30,433
Manuel is still in the ICU.

240
00:15:30,567 --> 00:15:33,100
He still needs close monitoring.

241
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:35,500
You know very well
that it will take a long time.

242
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:38,967
Yeah, I understand, Doc.

243
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:41,267
I just want to know...

244
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:45,233
the soonest time you estimate
I can take him home.

245
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:47,300
Because I know Manuel.

246
00:15:47,433 --> 00:15:49,133
He doesn't like this
kind of environment.

247
00:15:49,267 --> 00:15:50,600
He feels suffocated,

248
00:15:50,733 --> 00:15:52,567
just like when he got
hospitalized in Canada.

249
00:15:52,700 --> 00:15:56,200
That's why I want to transfer
him to a normal environment.

250
00:15:56,333 --> 00:15:58,867
Well, if I may suggest,
let's relax for now.

251
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,433
Manuel needs time, okay?

252
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:02,700
- Excuse me.
- Thank you, Doc.

253
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,767
You're rushing even the doctor?

254
00:16:09,933 --> 00:16:10,867
What do you think you're doing?

255
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,233
I have to, Alice.

256
00:16:12,367 --> 00:16:14,233
It'll be easier
to control Manuel

257
00:16:14,367 --> 00:16:16,333
once I get him out of here.

258
00:16:18,267 --> 00:16:19,667
Besides,

259
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,400
those who try to steal
my and Jessica's place

260
00:16:21,533 --> 00:16:24,267
will lose their chance.

261
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,400
And how will you do that?

262
00:16:26,533 --> 00:16:29,200
It'll be easier for them
to storm into the apartment.

263
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:31,900
At least this place has
guards who will stop them

264
00:16:32,033 --> 00:16:35,600
if they insist on going, despite
having a restraining order.

265
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:42,400
Who told you...

266
00:16:42,567 --> 00:16:44,367
I'd bring him to the apartment?

267
00:16:46,567 --> 00:16:48,667
I'll bring him somewhere...

268
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,600
no one knows.

269
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:36,467
Please let us know right away
what Manuel needs.

270
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:40,700
And let us know if
the doctor has new instructions.

271
00:17:45,567 --> 00:17:48,800
- Hello, Mom?
- Yes, dear? How is he doing?

272
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:51,200
Dad's okay now, Mom.

273
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:55,733
Thank you, Lord.
Dad's awake now.

274
00:17:55,867 --> 00:17:58,433
We'll go there later.

275
00:17:58,567 --> 00:18:01,667
How? Don't we have
a restraining order?

276
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:03,600
Andrea, no.
We'll do something about it.

277
00:18:03,733 --> 00:18:05,733
What are you going to do, Jeff?

278
00:18:05,867 --> 00:18:08,833
I'm having a hard time here.

279
00:18:08,967 --> 00:18:11,733
I keep sneaking in
just to see him.

280
00:18:11,867 --> 00:18:15,933
If I have to get Jessica
in on it, then so be it.

281
00:18:17,267 --> 00:18:18,533
Alright, Mom.

282
00:18:18,667 --> 00:18:20,400
I'll talk to her, too.

283
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:23,700
I'll call you right away, okay?

284
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:25,167
Okay, dear.

285
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:45,467
You've made huge progress,
Sir Manuel.

286
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:46,700
Keep getting better

287
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:49,800
so we can move you
to the regular room soon.

288
00:18:49,933 --> 00:18:51,100
Nurse?

289
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:55,467
Could you possibly lend
me your cell phone?

290
00:18:55,633 --> 00:18:57,467
I just want to call my family.

291
00:18:57,600 --> 00:19:00,800
Sorry, Sir.
Cellphones aren't allowed here.

292
00:19:02,067 --> 00:19:03,567
You brought one with you.

293
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:07,967
Oh, sorry.
I forgot to take it off earlier.

294
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:11,767
Nurse, don't worry.
I won't report you.

295
00:19:12,533 --> 00:19:15,100
Just let me borrow your phone.

296
00:19:15,233 --> 00:19:17,033
Please, just one call.

297
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:25,133
- Nurse, are you done?
- Yes, Ma'am.

298
00:19:25,267 --> 00:19:27,433
- Alright then. Leave us now.
- I'll leave you now.

299
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,667
Manuel?

300
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:34,700
How are you feeling?

301
00:19:49,433 --> 00:19:51,367
Andrea, you're not
supposed to be seen with me.

302
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:52,800
- There's a restraining...
- I know.

303
00:19:55,067 --> 00:19:57,900
I was going to ask you
for help again.

304
00:19:59,100 --> 00:19:59,967
About Dad?

305
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,467
Yeah, but...

306
00:20:02,633 --> 00:20:06,233
not for me anymore.
For Mom or Jeffrey.

307
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:10,333
I'm sorry, sis.

308
00:20:10,467 --> 00:20:12,600
But I can't do
that anymore.

309
00:20:16,367 --> 00:20:18,800
Please, Jessica.
I'm begging you.

310
00:20:18,933 --> 00:20:20,800
Come on, Jessica.

311
00:20:20,933 --> 00:20:22,467
Jessica. Please.

312
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,200
Please.

313
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:26,567
I'm begging you.

314
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,067
For Mom.

315
00:20:29,167 --> 00:20:32,033
She really wants to talk to Dad.

316
00:20:32,167 --> 00:20:33,500
Please.

317
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:35,633
I don't know.

318
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:40,200
I don't know how to get
Aunt Felma into the ICU.

319
00:20:40,333 --> 00:20:43,067
When it was you,
I used my name to request it.

320
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,467
But with Aunt Felma...

321
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:46,367
Jessica, let's take a chance.

322
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:48,900
Here's what we'll do.

323
00:20:49,033 --> 00:20:50,767
I'll go in again.

324
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:56,200
Mom.

325
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:57,533
Mommy.

326
00:20:57,667 --> 00:20:58,500
Mommy.

327
00:20:58,633 --> 00:20:59,833
How dare you try to
corrupt my child!

328
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:01,567
Mom, don't!

329
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:05,833
Let go of me!

330
00:21:05,967 --> 00:21:09,333
Mommy, please don't!

331
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:11,267
Who are you to boss
my daughter around?

332
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:13,367
Let go of me, Jessica!

333
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:15,833
You won't get near my husband.

334
00:21:15,967 --> 00:21:18,100
You won't get near him!

335
00:21:18,233 --> 00:21:19,700
Mommy, stop!

336
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:21,967
Andrea!

337
00:21:22,100 --> 00:21:23,433
- Mom, no!
- Let go of me!

338
00:21:28,733 --> 00:21:29,767
Traitor!

339
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:34,767
Why is it so hard for you
to take my side?

340
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:36,567
Am I really that horrible?

341
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:38,600
You'd rather defend them?

342
00:21:38,733 --> 00:21:40,967
Mommy!

343
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:42,800
You want to get hurt?
Is that what you want?

344
00:21:42,967 --> 00:21:44,867
Mommy!

345
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,000
You want this, huh?

346
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:48,167
- This is what you want, right?
- Mom!

347
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:49,333
- This is what you want?
- Mom!

348
00:21:49,467 --> 00:21:52,033
- You'd still defend them?
- Mom!

349
00:21:52,167 --> 00:21:54,767
Don't!

350
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:58,600
Help me!

351
00:21:58,733 --> 00:22:00,000
Please!

352
00:22:07,667 --> 00:22:09,433
Then you leave me
with no choice.

353
00:22:10,533 --> 00:22:11,567
- Andrea!
- Mommy, don't!

354
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:12,733
Andrea!

355
00:22:12,867 --> 00:22:14,333
Andrea, you need to know!

356
00:22:14,467 --> 00:22:16,233
Jessica isn't your
father's daughter!

357
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:23,867
- She's not your sister!
- Mom! Mom! No!

358
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,633
You think I won't do it?

359
00:22:25,767 --> 00:22:27,367
You think I'm just bluffing?

360
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:28,300
I'll tell them.

361
00:22:28,433 --> 00:22:30,700
I'll tell them
who you really are.

362
00:22:30,833 --> 00:22:35,600
- Andrea!
- Mom, please!

363
00:22:35,733 --> 00:22:37,167
I'll stay away, Mom.

364
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:38,800
I'll stay away.

365
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:44,300
Mommy, please!

366
00:22:44,433 --> 00:22:47,433
Mommy!

367
00:22:47,567 --> 00:22:50,367
I don't know, Jessica.

368
00:22:50,533 --> 00:22:52,833
I don't even know if...
I can still trust you.

369
00:22:52,967 --> 00:22:55,200
I don't even know
if I can still trust you.

370
00:22:57,567 --> 00:22:59,667
But maybe...

371
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:03,167
maybe I'll believe you...

372
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:05,867
if you do what I want.

373
00:23:08,033 --> 00:23:12,333
I'll only believe you if
you do everything I say.

374
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:14,700
If not, I'll tell them.
I'll tell them everything.

375
00:23:15,767 --> 00:23:18,633
-I'm sorry, but I'll them...
- No! Please!

376
00:23:18,767 --> 00:23:19,967
Mommy, please!

377
00:23:20,867 --> 00:23:24,467
I'll do everything you want.
I promise, Mommy!

378
00:23:35,900 --> 00:23:38,233
Mommy, please.

379
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:41,833
Hazel...

380
00:23:41,967 --> 00:23:45,000
DAMA? Discharge Against
Medical Advice?

381
00:23:45,133 --> 00:23:46,767
You're taking Manuel home?

382
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:48,100
Yes, Doc.

383
00:23:48,233 --> 00:23:50,100
Manuel really wants to go home.

384
00:23:50,233 --> 00:23:51,800
We've talked about it.

385
00:23:51,933 --> 00:23:54,000
When did he sign this?

386
00:23:54,133 --> 00:23:57,900
Earlier, when Nurse Gayle
did her rounds.

387
00:23:59,133 --> 00:24:00,767
Doc...

388
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:04,767
I'll take care of him.
I'll watch him 24/7.

389
00:24:04,900 --> 00:24:06,467
And don't worry,

390
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,600
I will not hold you
and the hospital liable

391
00:24:08,733 --> 00:24:09,967
if anything happens.

392
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:12,200
Hazel, it's not that.

393
00:24:12,333 --> 00:24:14,633
Yes, Manuel is improving.

394
00:24:14,767 --> 00:24:18,033
The problem is, his case
is extremely sensitive.

395
00:24:18,167 --> 00:24:20,767
One wrong move
and he could desaturate.

396
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:23,467
He's still on a chest tube,
still draining.

397
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:25,733
Doctor, I can handle it.

398
00:24:25,867 --> 00:24:27,633
Why else did I become a nurse?

399
00:24:27,767 --> 00:24:30,667
I'll buy him oxygen
and everything else he needs.

400
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:32,167
I'll take care of him.

401
00:24:32,300 --> 00:24:33,233
It's not just that.

402
00:24:33,367 --> 00:24:37,133
Discharging him
against medical advice, DAMA,

403
00:24:37,267 --> 00:24:38,700
is incredibly risky.

404
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:41,000
Manuel is also my
responsibility.

405
00:24:41,133 --> 00:24:43,800
He knows that, Doc. He's aware.

406
00:24:43,933 --> 00:24:45,967
But what can I do?

407
00:24:46,100 --> 00:24:47,933
He really doesn't want
to stay here anymore.

408
00:24:48,067 --> 00:24:50,033
I told you before, right?

409
00:24:50,167 --> 00:24:52,367
He feels suffocated
in the hospital.

410
00:24:55,367 --> 00:24:57,700
Doc, please trust me.

411
00:24:58,767 --> 00:25:01,600
I just want to make
it up to my husband.

412
00:25:01,733 --> 00:25:04,667
He's taken such good care of me
since the day we got married.

413
00:25:04,833 --> 00:25:06,633
And now...

414
00:25:06,767 --> 00:25:08,467
it's my turn
to take care of him.

415
00:25:08,600 --> 00:25:10,000
Doctor,

416
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:12,233
I know what I'm doing.

417
00:25:12,367 --> 00:25:14,767
And, may I ask a favor?

418
00:25:14,900 --> 00:25:16,267
A special one.

419
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:20,400
If Manuel or I
have any questions,

420
00:25:20,533 --> 00:25:22,067
can we call you?

421
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:23,067
Please, Doc.

422
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:24,900
If it's not too much to ask.

423
00:25:25,967 --> 00:25:28,500
Okay, okay.

424
00:25:28,633 --> 00:25:29,500
Call me.

425
00:25:29,633 --> 00:25:31,800
Every little thing, update me.

426
00:25:31,933 --> 00:25:34,100
Please. Okay, Hazel?

427
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:36,067
Yes, of course, Doc. I will.

428
00:25:36,233 --> 00:25:38,100
I'll even video call
you if I need to.

429
00:25:38,233 --> 00:25:40,367
Alright.

430
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:41,800
We'll get this done.

431
00:25:41,933 --> 00:25:43,333
Thank you, Doctor.

432
00:25:45,667 --> 00:25:47,367
Jessica?

433
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:49,333
- Careful.
- Jessica, where are you going?

434
00:25:49,467 --> 00:25:50,733
Dad!

435
00:25:50,867 --> 00:25:51,967
Where will you take my father?

436
00:25:52,100 --> 00:25:53,200
Let go of me!

437
00:25:53,333 --> 00:25:54,267
Wait!

438
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:55,433
Dad!

439
00:25:55,567 --> 00:25:57,900
Why did you let Hazel
take Manuel out of the hospital?

440
00:25:58,033 --> 00:26:01,100
He just had surgery
a few days ago!

441
00:26:01,233 --> 00:26:04,367
We were only following
the patient's wishes.

442
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:07,700
He signed the Discharge
Against Medical Advice form.

443
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:09,900
Manuel signed it himself?

444
00:26:10,067 --> 00:26:10,900
Yes, Ma'am.

445
00:26:11,033 --> 00:26:12,367
Mom? What's that?

446
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:14,300
Something to help
your dad sleep longer.

447
00:26:14,433 --> 00:26:16,300
He needs plenty of rest.

448
00:26:16,433 --> 00:26:17,500
Aunt Felma...

449
00:26:17,633 --> 00:26:19,967
Jessica, where
did you take Dad?

450
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:24,067
Hazel never should've taken
Manuel out of the hospital.

451
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:26,733
Jessica, where are you?
